# 20. 悔やむと書いてミライ

Ena: Sigh... Did this really change anything? It's all such a pain in the ass.
Mizuki: Come on, don't get too upset. You're glad everything worked out, aren't you?
Ena: Maybe...
Kanade: Oh, that reminds me. I listened to all of OWN's songs.
???: I see.
Kanade: I knew I could feel you in them. They sounded just like you.
???: Is that so?
???: Could you tell me something?
Kanade: Huh?
???: What kind of sound do I have?
Miku: I'm so glad you were able to find your true feelings.
Miku: Now we can finally sing together.
Kanade: Huh?
Miku: Your true feelings are about to give birth to a new song. Look.
Ena: Can you hear that?
Mizuki: Is this what you mentioned before, Miku?
???: This song is my true feelings? But I still haven't found anything yet.
Miku: That's not true. You've found it, Mafuyu.
Miku: This SEKAI, and the song within it, are proof of that.
???: My feelings...are here?
Miku: Yes. So let's sing together.
???: Miku...
Miku: Yes?
???: Thank you...
Miku: Come...let's all sing together.
Ena: Huh? Why do we have to sing as well?
Miku: Without all of you, she would not have been able to find her true feelings.
Miku: I want to thank all three of you for coming here.
Ena: I-I only came here to give her a piece of my mind.
Mizuki: Thanks for coming, Enanan♪
Ena: Hearing that from you is so annoying.
Mizuki: What?! Meanie!
Miku: Hehe.
Kanade: Come on, Yuki. Let's sing.
???: Okay.
???: Oh, I finally see.
???: I wanted somebody to find me. Isn't that right, Miku?
Kanade: <Huh? When did I...?>
Mizuki: <We're back! Is everyone here?>
Ena: <Yeah, I'm back.>
Kanade: <What about Yuki?>
Kanade, Mizuki & Ena: <.....>
???: <I'm here.>
Mizuki: <Yuki!>
Kanade: <Good. I'm glad.>
Mizuki: <Oh! Hey, take a look at the shared folder!>
Ena: <Ouch! Don't suddenly yell like that! Now what's this about the shared folder? Huh?>
Ena: <The name of that “Untitled” file changed?>
Kanade: <“Composing the Future”?>
???: <Miku said that once I found my true feelings, they would give birth to a new song.>
Kanade: <Then this is that song?>
???: <Yeah.>
Ena: <Does that mean we can finally put this whole mess behind us? What a relief...>
Ena: <Yuki, you sure caused us a heap of trouble.>
Mizuki: <You say that, but you still came running to help in the end♪>
Ena: <I already told you I just went to tell her off!>
Ena: <And I'm still mad, just so you know.>
Ena: <Still, I'm looking forward to working together again, Yuki.>
Mizuki: <Yeah. Welcome back, Yuki.>
???: <Thanks.>
Kanade: <It's going to be morning soon. We should call it a night. I want to get some sleep so we can start working on our next song tomorrow.>
Ena: <You're right. Besides, I'm actually super tired.>
Kanade: <Alright, see—>
Mizuki: <Hey, hold on!>
Kanade: <What?>
Ena: <What is it, Amia?>
Mizuki: <There's a little something I want to suggest...>
Kanade: Good morning, Dad.
Kanade's Father: .....
Kanade: He's sleeping again.
Kanade: I just wanted you to know, Dad. Something great happened.
Kanade: I met a girl a little like myself and wrote a song for her.
Kanade: She never did listen to it, but in the end she was still able to find something important to her.
Kanade: Her true feelings...and her true song.
Kanade: I'm still not able to save anyone with my music.
Kanade: But I'll keep composing.
Kanade: So one day, I'd like you to listen to it again.
Kanade's Father: .....
Kanade: I have somewhere to be, so I should get going. I'll see you later.
Kanade's Father: Kanade...
Kanade: Huh?
Kanade: Dad? Did you say something?
Kanade's Father: .....
Kanade: Oh... He's just talking in his sleep?
Kanade: But still... That was nice.
Kanade: It's been a while since I've heard you say my name.
